@startuml Fig_3_3_2_Training_Process_Workflow
title Fig 3.3.2: Training Process Workflow (train.py + SLMConfig)

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE

start

:Load **SLMConfig**\n(seed, batch, block_size, LR schedule params);
:Set device (CUDA/CPU),\n**autocast** dtype (e.g. bfloat16),\noptional **GradScaler** (float16);

:Instantiate **BinDataLoader**\nmemmap **train.bin** / **val.bin**;
:Build **SLM** model,\n**configure_optimizers** (AdamW);

if (Resume from **checkpoints/best.pt**?) then (yes)
  :Load model + optimizer state,\nrestore iter / best val loss;
endif

if (**torch.compile** enabled on CUDA?) then (yes)
  :Wrap model (optional);
endif

repeat
  :Compute **lr** = warmup +\ncosine decay (**get_lr**);

  if (iter > 0 AND iter % **eval_interval**?) then (yes)
    :**model.eval()** + **no_grad**;
    :**estimate_loss** on train & val\n(**eval_iters** batches each);
    :Append row to **logs/train_log.csv**;
    if (val_loss improves?) then (yes)
      :Save **checkpoints/best.pt**\n(raw state_dict, optimizer,\nconfig snapshot);
    endif
    :**model.train()**;
  endif

  :**optimizer.zero_grad**;
  repeat :Micro-step 1..**gradient_accumulation_steps**;
    :Sample batch (**x**, **y**)\nfrom train memmap;
    :Forward **SLM(x, y)** → logits, **cross-entropy** loss;
    :**loss / grad_accum_steps** → **backward**;
    :Prefetch next batch;
  repeat while (micro-steps done?)

  if (**grad_clip** > 0?) then (yes)
    :**clip_grad_norm_**;
  endif

  :**optimizer.step** (+ scaler step if float16);

  if (iter % **log_interval**?) then (yes)
    :Console log:\nloss, lr, ms/iter, tokens/sec;
  endif

  if (iter > 0 AND iter % 1000?) then (yes)
    :Save **checkpoints/latest.pt**;
  endif

repeat while (iter <= **max_iters**?) is (no) not (yes)

:Training complete\n(report best val loss);

stop

@enduml
